{
  "texts": [
    "They achieved a 12% reduction of total costs.",
    "The authors measured adherence to feedback by dividing the number of tests authorized the day before (during audit) by the real number of tests effectively requested.",
    "Compliance was low (51%), indicating that twice as many tests were requested as the previous day.",
    "Compliance to feedback is an interesting parameter to measure, and would be instructive to assess in interventional studies using A&F strategies.",
    "Likewise, safety outcomes and effect persistence over time are rarely measured [34], which can nevertheless provide interesting information."
  ]
}